# VulkanDesktop — Comment conventions

Apply when adding or editing comments in `VulkanDesktop/` (C++, GLSL). Prefer **English** in source; keep comments **short and purposeful**.

## When to comment

| Do comment | Do not comment |
|------------|----------------|
| Shader ↔ CPU struct layout, descriptor bindings, packed fields | What the next line obviously does |
| Queue-family / sharing-mode / frame-in-flight rules | Restating parameter names |
| Non-obvious conventions (light direction, UV flip, Z-up) | Tutorial “Step #1 … Step #N” unless teaching |
| Stubs, TODOs, known tech debt (with **why**) | Deleted or misleading legacy notes |
| `BeginFrame` ordering, ImGui vs camera input | Every Vulkan struct field |

## Formats

**File header** (optional, top of `.cpp` / complex `.h`):

```cpp
// Module: Vk_Core — Vulkan device, swapchain, frame loop, resource helpers.
```

**Section** (major phases only):

```cpp
// --- Frame loop (CPU) ---
```

**Single-line** (default):

```cpp
// One uniform buffer slab; per-frame slice via dynamic offset (see PadUniformBufferSize).
```

**Contract / pitfall** (high-signal):

```cpp
// CONTRACT: eVk_* bindings must match TriangleVertex.vert / TriangleFrag_Lit.frag layout(binding = N).
// WARNING: texcoord_index may be -1; never index attrib.texcoords without a guard.
```

**TODO**:

```cpp
// TODO(draw-stream): wire DrawObjects or remove; RecordCommandBuffer is the live path.
```

## Domain rules

- **Gpu* / UBO**: Document `std140` layout, which shader `register` it maps to, and any **repurposed** fields (e.g. `myFogDistance` packs material params).
- **Descriptors**: Binding index + type + stage; keep in sync with `Vk_Enum.h` and GLSL shaders.
- **Queues**: State when graphics doubles as transfer; when `CONCURRENT` vs `EXCLUSIVE` sharing applies.
- **Coordinates**: Z-up world, Y-flipped Vulkan projection (`proj[1][1] *= -1`), sunlight “toward sun” direction.
- **Paths**: Note dependency on working directory only at resolution sites (`UtilLoader::ResolvePath`), not at every `ReadFile` call.

## Cleanup

- Fix typos in comments when touching a function (`Upadate` → `Update`, etc.).
- Remove comments that contradict the code; update or delete.
- Replace vague `// TODO:` with scoped `// TODO(area): reason`.

